name: Broccoli Rabe
description: Broccoli rabe is even more nutritionally dense than broccoli.

name: Cabbage
description: Cabbage provides a decent source of vitamins C and K1, and it may potentially lower cancer risk.

name: Carrots
description: Carrots are a root vegetable that supply a decent source of beta-carotenoids.

name: Coconut Water
description: Coconut water is a clear liquid found within fresh coconuts.it's a refreshing drink for those who enjoy the taste.

name: Fruit Juice
description: It's much easier to consume too many calories from a few glasses of fruit juice per day than it is by eating multiple whole fruits.

name: Soda/Soft Drinks
description: Diet soda drinks made with a sweetener are likely healthier alternatives to sugar-sweetened beverages.

name: Plant Milks
description: Plant-based milks are often devised to have a similar nutritional profile to regular dairy milk. they are usually fortified with vitamin B12 and vitamin D.

name: Milk and Dairy Drinks
description: Milkshakes are another trendy dairy drink, but they often contain large amounts of added sugar (and calories).

name: Cherry
description: Cherry contains lots of antioxidants that may help reduce the risk of cancer and cardiovascular disease.

name: Blackberry
description: It has many health benefits, including being good for your skin and helping to lower blood pressure.

name: Antep Pistachios
description: Due to the ideal climate and great soil conditions, these pistachios have a vibrant green color and an intense, complex, and citrusy flavor.

name: Brazil Nut
description: They improve heart health, help with regulating skin-related problems, stimulate the digestive system, boost the immune system, and improve hormone function.

name: Mocktail
description: It is a cocktail made with non-alcoholic ingredients, rather than with alcohol.
